AB I examine how the choice controversy--conceptualized in sociology as the
   structure-agency debate and in criminology as the determinism-free will
   debate--has been depicted in 53 criminology textbooks published from
   1956 to 1965 and from 1983 to 1992.  My data show that despite dramatic
