   important disciplinary differences in its construction, adoption, and
   diffusion. We reformulate feminist phase theory in paradigm shift terms,
   then operationalize and contrast two versions of it. Our analysis and
   review indicate that the missing variable in women's studies
   transformation projects is the participants' discipline. Data from our
