   reputational standing. Examination of Parsons's involvement in the local
   Harvard network indicates that contemporary reputational judgments
   decisively affected his choice of intellectual predecessors. This
   analysis also brings to light the organizational and institutional
   conditions under which a "reputational model" is required to understand
